column1: #Text=While known primarily as a gateway to Mexico , its small downtown core has a few well-preserved examples of early 20th-century architecture .
#Text=The town is also noted as the temporary residence of Thornton Wilder , who wrote most of his classic 1967 novel The Eighth Day while based here .
#Text=Offers a helpful map for walking tours .
#Text=Douglas is most easily reached by driving Highway 80 or Highway 191 south from I-10 .
#Text=The town is pedestrian-friendly , and most sights and restaurants are within easy walking distance .
#Text=There is no public transportation , so a car is needed to go further afield .
#Text=On the National Register of Historic Places , Ginger Rogers , Anna Pavlova , and John Philip Sousa all performed here .
#Text=The theatre was closed in 1958 , and after decades of neglect is undergoing a complete restoration .
#Text=It is not yet open to the public , but the ornate facade can be appreciated from the outside .
#Text=A small museum displaying historic photographs and memorabilia from the area .
#Text=Border Air Museum , E 10th St and Airport Rd , ☏ +1 520-364-2478 .
#Text=A small museum dedicated to the history of cross-border aviation in Douglas .
#Text=Cochise County Fair , 3677 N Leslie Canyon Rd , ☏ +1 520-364-3819 . all day .
#Text=Attractions include animal exhibits , amusement rides , and rodeo events . $ 6 ( adults ) .
#Text=As a gateway to Mexico , many visitors walk across the border to Agua Prieta for the day , which has a number of curio and souvenir shops .
#Text=A very popular Mexican fast-food restaurant , with good burritos , flautas , and caldos ( soups ) .
#Text=The service can be a little disorganized , but the food is worth the wait .
#Text=Casa Segovia ( formerly El Conquistador Restaurant ) , 1046 G Ave ( Gadsden Hotel ) , ☏ +1 520-364-1169 .
#Text=Hotel restaurant operated by the local restaurateur Segovia family .
#Text=For more details about the Gadsden Hotel , see listing below .
#Text=Chatitas Mexican Restaurant , 301 E 10th St ( entrance on Pan American Ave ) , ☏ +1 520-364-1144 .
#Text=One of the most popular Mexican restaurants in town .
#Text=Good Mexican food , particularly popular for breakfast .
#Text=Service can sometimes be a bit spotty , but the food is usually very good .
#Text=Surprisingly authentic Indian food , particularly popular for breakfast and brunches .
#Text=Can cook up vegetarian meals on request .
#Text=Saddle & Spur Tavern , 1046 G Ave ( Gadsden Hotel ) , ☏ +1 520-364-4481 .
#Text=Known for the assortment of cattle brands displayed on the walls .
#Text=For a description of the hotel , see listing below .
#Text=A National Historic site which in its heyday hosted the likes of John Wayne , Spencer Tracy , and Thornton Wilder .
#Text=It is widely believed to be haunted by several ghosts , one of them headless .
#Text=The mezzanine features a 42-foot long Tiffany stained glass mural as well as an Italian marble staircase , and has featured in several films .
#Text=Has an outdoor pool and free Wi-Fi , as well as on-site restaurant .
#Text=Southeast Arizona Medical Center , 2174 W Oak Ave ( corner of N County Hospital Rd ) , ☏ +1 520-364-7931 .
